• Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. CAPE TOWN - Communication Minister Nomvula Mokonyane will brief the media following Cabinet's regular meeting this week. Health services in the North West Province have been brought to a halt following political upheaval and violence. Mokonyane is expected to detail Cabinet’s discussions surrounding North West Premier Supra Mahumapelo, who effective from Wednesday, took leave of absence from office. There is also uncertainty as to whether President Cyril Ramaphosa will visit the province again anytime soon. eNCA